\begin_layout Standard
The 
\family typewriter
optimize4
\family default
 package facilitates the solution of optimization problems,
 with a particular focus on shape optimization problems for which 
\emph on
morpho
\emph default
 was designed.
 The design separates 
\emph on
what
\emph default
 is being optimized (an 
\emph on
OptimizationProblem
\emph default
),
 
\emph on
how parameters are exposed
\emph default
 to an algorithm (an 
\emph on
OptimizationAdapter
\emph default
),
 and 
\emph on
how the algorithm proceeds
\emph default
 (an 
\emph on
OptimizationController
\emph default
).
 To use the package,
 import it as usual:
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

import optimize4
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This imports three subsidiary modules that work together (Fig.
 ).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
OptimizationProblem describes energies and constraints using morpho Functionals.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
OptimizationAdapter reads and writes degrees of freedom,
 and evaluates the objective,
 constraints,
 and derivatives.
 Adapters can be chained (penalty methods,
 fixing variables,
 caching,
 and so on).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
OptimizationController implements an optimization algorithm by calling adapter methods and updating parameters.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A typical mesh problem:
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

var problem = OptimizationProblem(mesh)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

problem.addEnergy(Length())
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

problem.addConstraint(AreaEnclosed())
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

var adapter = ProblemAdapter(problem,
 mesh)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

var opt = SQPController(adapter)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

opt.optimize(500)
\end_layout

\end_inset

A field problem optimizes degrees of freedom stored in a 
\family typewriter
Field
\family default
 rather than mesh vertex positions:
\begin_inset listings
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

var problem = OptimizationProblem(mesh)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

problem.addEnergy(GradSq(phi))
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

var adapter = ProblemAdapter(problem,
 phi)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

var opt = LBFGSController(adapter)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

opt.optimize(500)
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

